<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="AppDiffLinApprox" checkit-title="Linear Approximation">
    <statement>
        <p>
A certain function <m>p(x)</m> satisfies
<m>p(-7) = -44</m> and <m>p'(-7) = 7</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
Explain how to find the local linearization <m>L(x)</m>
of <m>p(x)</m> at <m>-7</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Explain how to estimate the value of <m>p(-6.975)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Suppose that <m>p'(-7)=0</m> and you know that
<m>p''(x) &lt; 0</m> for <m>x &gt; -7</m>.
Explain how to determine if your estimate of <m>p(-6.975)</m>
is too large or too small.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Suppose that <m>p''(x) &gt; 0</m> for <m>x &lt; -7</m>.
Use this fact and the additional information above to sketch an accurate
graph of <m>y=p(x)</m> near <m>x=-7</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li><p><m>L(x)=7 \, x + 5</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>p(-6.975) \approx -43.8276</m></p></li>
            <li><p>The estimate is too small.</p></li>
            <li><p>N/A</p></li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
